#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""Multi-agent collaboration task tracker CLI for AI/human agents.

Key properties:
- Pure Python standard library (no external dependencies).
- Stores its state in a JSON file in the current working directory by default.
- File-based locking to avoid corruption when multiple agents modify the board.
- JSON-only, deterministic output tuned for LLM / agent consumption.
- Supports task leasing so agents can "pull" work without collisions.
- Adds explicit multi-agent collaboration metadata, events, and per-agent plans.

Design goals:
- Simple, explicit commands (read, add, update, move, pull, release, delete,
  init, schema, relate, log, events, agent-touch, agent-view, plan).
- No dependence on stable agent IDs; leases use whatever identifier
  the caller provides.
- All commands are idempotent where practical, safe to call from tools.
"""

